  "prompt": "Which Pakistani universities are recognized by Australian immigration department?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several Pakistani universities are recognized by the Australian Department of Home Affairs for immigration purposes, particularly for skilled migration visas. Recognition can change, so it\u2019s essential to verify the list directly with the current regulations from the Australian immigration authorities or consult with a registered migration agent.\n\nGenerally, the following Pakistani universities have been recognized:\n\n1. **Quaid-i-Azam University, Islamabad**\n2. **University of the Punjab, Lahore**\n3. **University of Karachi**\n4. **National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST), Islamabad**\n5. **Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS)**\n6. **University of Engineering and Technology (UET), Lahore**\n7. **Pakistan Institute of Engineering and Applied Sciences (PIEAS)**\n\nPlease ensure to check the latest updates from the Australian Department of Home Affairs or the relevant professional assessing bodies like Engineers Australia, or the Australian Computer Society, depending on your field of study and profession.",
